## Key Exception

This scene has a non-standard lower-row working height by client request.

Observed height stack:

- `160` plinth/support zone.
- `770` lower cabinet/body zone.
- `20` countertop thickness.
- Working height: `950`.

Do not normalize this project back to the common `100/770/38 -> 908` or `100/770/30 -> 900` pattern. Here the lower body still reads as a 770 module family. The module carcass/body must not be stretched; the total working height is raised by increasing the support/plinth zone to 160 and using the 20mm stone top.

Because the countertop is 20mm, classify it as stone.

