## Template / Standards Takeaways

- Add explicit custom-height handling: store the declared/observed height stack instead of forcing standard lower-row heights. Raise/lower the working height through supports/plinth, not by changing the cabinet body height.
- For 20mm/30mm countertops: classify as stone, then compute target working height from client/project rule, not from a fixed base standard.
- `160 + 770 + 20 = 950` is a valid observed finished-project pattern when client-requested: 160 support/plinth, 770 module body, 20 stone top.
- Upper start height and backsplash/profiles must be evaluated relative to the raised worktop height.
- Real corner module `BG1#3` can have bbox height `930` when the lower row is raised; do not compare corner height to standard scenes without accounting for plinth/top stack.
- Keep lighting audit section: even scenes without visible render lights may use recessed profile components with nested diffuser/LED variants.

